  "description": "A ring $(R, +, cdot, 0, 1)$ is a set equipped with two binary operations — addition and multiplication — such that $(R, +, 0)$ is an [abelian group](./abelian-group.md), $(R, cdot, 1)$ is a [monoid](./monoid.md), and multiplication distributes over addition on both sides.",
